cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DS

The paper discusses automated data-driven decision-making systems that use learning algorithms and available data to optimize decision support assistance. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of fairness in decision-making, which is a growing concern in the field of computational social science (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper proposes a learning mechanism for decision tree induction over streams, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
